  "prompt": "How can you lock a Macbook Pro?",
  "response": "Locking a MacBook Pro is a simple process. You have a few options to quickly secure your device:\n\n### Option 1: Using Keyboard Shortcut\n1. **Keyboard Shortcut**: Press `Control + Command + Q` simultaneously. This will lock your screen immediately and require your password to unlock.\n\n### Option 2: Through the Apple Menu\n1. **Apple Menu**: Click on the Apple logo in the top-left corner of the screen.\n2. Select `Lock Screen` from the dropdown menu.\n\n### Option 3: Using Hot Corners\n1. **Hot Corners**: This method involves setting up a \"hot corner\" that will lock your screen when you move your mouse to a specified corner.\n   - Open `System Preferences`.\n   - Navigate to `Mission Control`.\n   - Click the `Hot Corners` button.\n   - Choose a corner and select `Lock Screen` or `Put Display to Sleep`.\n\n### Option 4: Using Touch Bar (if applicable)\n1. **Touch Bar**: If your MacBook Pro has a Touch Bar, you can add a lock screen button.\n   - Open `System Preferences`.\n   - Navigate to `Keyboard`, then `Customize Control Strip`.\n   - Add the `Screen Lock` button to your Touch Bar.\n\n### Option 5: Using Terminal\n1. **Terminal**: Open the Terminal app and type the following command to lock your screen:\n   ```shell\n   /System/Library/CoreServices/Menu\\ Extras/User.menu/Contents/Resources/CGSession -suspend\n   ```\n\nAny of these methods will lock your MacBook Pro and require your password to unlock it.",
